# Byte-exact cross-language test vectors: never EOL-convert them. GitHub's
# Windows runners default to core.autocrlf=true, which rewrites checked-in LF
# files to CRLF on checkout — that breaks the vectors-lock test in
# remote::crypto::tests, which reads the file verbatim and compares it against
# its own '\n'-joined output. Treating the fixtures as binary keeps their bytes
# identical on every platform.
remote/protocol/tests/fixtures/e2e_crypto/** -text
